<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,461,919]" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,453,461,487]" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">Taxonomic discussion:</emphasis>
—The specimens kept at BASU, 
<emphasis box="[826,1031,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">M. Ranjbar 30880</emphasis>
, were determined morphologically as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Willdenow ex Roemer &amp; Schultes) Greuter &amp; Burdet" authorityName="Greuter &amp; Burdet" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow ex Roemer &amp; Schultes" box="[136,870,497,524]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Huynhia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[136,256,497,523]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">H. pulchra</emphasis>
(Willdenow ex Roemer &amp; Schultes) Greuter &amp; Burdet
</taxonomicName>
, which are confined to 
<collectingRegion box="[1133,1321,497,523]" country="Iran" name="Esfahan" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">Isfahan province</collectingRegion>
. Herbarium material of this species is very scarce. However, when the specimens were more thoroughly examined, several characters appeared to be dissimilar to that species and other closely related species. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter &amp; Burdet" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow ex Roemer &amp; Schultes" box="[1323,1444,569,595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Huynhia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[1323,1444,569,595]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">H. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially by its habit, indumentum, number of leaflets, and shape, size, and arrangement of pods, and also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter &amp; Burdet" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow ex Roemer &amp; Schultes" box="[136,255,641,667]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Huynhia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchra">
<emphasis box="[136,255,641,667]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">H. pulchra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by pollen shape, stigma shallowly bilobed, shorter style, smaller corolla, and calyx in anthesis. General and detailed characters of the vegetative parts and flowers in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1981" box="[763,858,677,703]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Huynhia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[763,858,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">Huynhia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are already well known from various literature. Here, two characters are worthy of mention because of their taxonomic significance; one concerning the androecial arrangement and other the stigma structure. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Greuter" authorityYear="1981" box="[507,602,749,775]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Huynhia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[507,602,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">Huynhia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the epipetalous stamens are inserted through very short filaments at different heights within the corolla tube, e.g., three higher at the throat and two lower down in the tube, however, this character also occurs in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Khatamsaz 2002)" baseAuthorityName="Khatamsaz" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[240,616,821,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Alkanna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frigida">
<emphasis box="[240,411,821,847]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="230">Alkanna frigida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Khatamsaz, M." box="[423,609,821,847]" pageId="14" pageNumber="230" refId="ref8404" refString="Khatamsaz, M. (2002) Boraginaceae. In: Assadi, M., Khatamsaz, M. &amp; Maassoumi, A. A. (Eds.) Flora of Iran, vol. 39. Research Institute of Forests and Rangelands, Tehran, Iran, 420 pp." type="book" year="2002">Khatamsaz 2002</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
